Topic: sdpub

sdpub Help Topic

Purpose:
  Explain the `.sdpub` archive model and route safe CLI operations.

Primary rule:
  Treat `.sdpub` as an LLM Wiki archive managed by SpineDigest commands.
  It is physically a ZIP archive, but agents should not unzip it or read `database.db` directly for routine retrieval.

Preferred top-level operations:
  - `spinedigest status <archive.sdpub>` for readiness and counts
  - `spinedigest index <archive.sdpub>` for entry points
  - `spinedigest list <archive.sdpub> ...` for bounded object discovery
  - `spinedigest find <archive.sdpub> <query>` for deterministic search
  - `spinedigest grep <archive.sdpub> <query>` for exact continuous text
  - `spinedigest page <archive.sdpub> <id>` for object details and local navigation
  - `spinedigest read <archive.sdpub> <id>` for continuous plain-text reading
  - `spinedigest evidence <archive.sdpub> <id>` for source backing
  - `spinedigest links/backlinks/path ...` for graph navigation
  - `spinedigest export <archive.sdpub> ...` for projections

Archive model:
  - The archive stores metadata, TOC chapters, normalized source fragments, graph nodes, graph edges, source evidence, and summaries.
  - Public object ids include chapter:<id>, node:<id>, fragment:<serial>:<fragment>, sentence:<serial>:<fragment>:<index>, summary:<id>, and meta:book.
  - Current editable archives are still maintained internally around chapters and graph nodes.

sdpub maintenance command family:
  `spinedigest sdpub ...` remains available for lower-level maintenance:
  - info, toc, list, cat, cover, meta
  - chapter add/remove/reset/set-source/set-summary/status/list
  - stage pending/advance
  - graph status/log/show/grep/neighbors/blame/path

LLM behavior:
  - Inspection, search, navigation, metadata edits, chapter tree edits, source edits, and export do not call an LLM provider.
  - `build`, `sdpub stage advance`, and graph/summary generation may call an LLM provider.
  - Run `spinedigest estimate <archive.sdpub>` before full-archive LLM-backed builds.

Mutation safety:
  - Mutating `sdpub` maintenance commands edit archives in place.
  - Do not run multiple mutating commands against the same archive concurrently.
  - Keep your own copy before destructive commands such as chapter remove or reset.

